code: public void testJarHellDetected() {     BuildResult result = GradleRunner.create().withProjectDir(getProjectDir("jarHell")).withArguments("clean", "precommit", "-s", "-Dlocal.repo.path=" + getLocalTestRepoPath()).withPluginClasspath().buildAndFail().     assertTaskFailed(result, ":jarHell").     assertOutputContains(result.getOutput(), "java.lang.IllegalStateException: jar hell!", "class: org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger"). }
